28/Oct/16 16:57;Xaerxess;If I understand correctly, you modify elements of your type {{MyClass}} after putting them into set? If so, you're violating set contract[1], which expects immutable elements (or at least in terms of equals and hashCode):

{quote}
Note: Great care must be exercised if mutable objects are used as set elements. The behavior of a set is not specified if the value of an object is changed in a manner that affects equals comparisons while the object is an element in the set. A special case of this prohibition is that it is not permissible for a set to contain itself as an element.
{quote}

[1]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/Set.html

